 Still, the measurement error for variables in any claimed relationship
 between identity and purchasing power in Africa can be severe - due to
 a bulky informal sector (which may have expanded due to recent economic
 developments), expansions in the areas of micro-credit as well as mass
 education 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "DolanBoP"

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "MeagherNigeria"

\end_inset

 and the complicated changes in identities themselves (which are homogenising
 with the expansion of internal trade
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\paragraph_spacing single
There are regional disparities in the foreign investment in sub-Saharan
