 This marks a preference towards industrial goods in the urban (expensive)
 areas.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing single
Another observation that presents an opportunity to combine status needs
 is that the scarcity of items occurs in clusters of objects.
 Carpets-rugs require a certain housing status and access to English depends
 on region.
 Similarly, many hobby equipment may require access to electricity etc.
 The clustering of these items essentially point to the urban-rural differences
 in the country.
 We also find that the prices can be significantly different between regions.
 The dummies 
