 One considers a multiplicative index 
\begin_inset Formula $m(a^{h},u^{h})$
\end_inset

such that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\paragraph_spacing single
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat}{1}
c^{h}(u^{h},p,a^{h}) & =m(a^{h},u^{h})\cdot c(u^{h},p)
\end{alignat}

\end_inset


\end_layout

